{"batch":"Design coherence — Mechanical Concern Signals","batch_index":9,"assessments":{"initialization_coupling":72.0},"dimension_notes":{"initialization_coupling":{"evidence":["Confirmed systemic mutable-global coupling: language/plugin bootstrapping relies on process-wide registries (`desloppify/languages/_framework/registry_state.py` and `desloppify/engine/hook_registry.py`) with mutable `_active_scope` and scope maps that are mutated during discovery.","Confirmed order-dependent split behavior: `load_all()` temporarily sets scoped active state then restores it (`desloppify/languages/_framework/discovery.py`), while detectors call `get_lang_hook(...)` without scope (`desloppify/engine/detectors/review_coverage.py`, `desloppify/engine/detectors/coverage/mapping.py`), so hook resolution can depend on prior import/registration order and trigger reload re-registration paths.","Confirmed root coupling bug: coverage mapping uses module-level `PROJECT_ROOT` constant (`desloppify/engine/detectors/coverage/mapping.py`) instead of runtime-aware `get_project_root()`, bypassing `RuntimeContext.project_root` (`desloppify/core/_internal/text_utils.py`) and making path normalization sensitive to initialization state.","Confirmed additional startup-state coupling via mutable path overrides (`desloppify/core/paths_api.py`) plus import-time root snapshot in CLI (`desloppify/cli.py`), creating hidden dependence on when globals are set relative to command execution.","Refuted workflow-loop concern for reviewed orchestration paths: reruns are explicitly gated on drained backlog unless `--force-review-rerun` (`desloppify/app/commands/review/preflight.py`), and follow-up scan is skipped when batch failures remain (`desloppify/app/commands/review/batches.py`), reducing churn loops in the examined flow.","Refuted several seed mechanical design flags as non-init-coupling defects in this batch: `plan/synthesis/organize.py`, `plan/synthesis/reflect.py`, and `plan/synthesize_handlers.py` are large/branchy but enforce staged gates rather than introducing startup-order coupling."],"impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"architectural_change","confidence":"high"}},"findings":[{"dimension":"initialization_coupling","identifier":"hook_registry_scope_split_brain","summary":"Hook registration and lookup use different implicit scopes, creating order-dependent initialization","related_files":["desloppify/languages/_framework/discovery.py","desloppify/engine/hook_registry.py","desloppify/languages/csharp/__init__.py","desloppify/engine/detectors/review_coverage.py"],"evidence":["`load_all()` sets hook registry active scope to project root only during plugin import, then restores prior scope (`discovery.py`), so scoped entries are transiently active during registration.","Language modules register hooks at import time via `register_lang_hooks(\"...\")` with no explicit scope (`languages/*/__init__.py`), binding to whatever implicit scope is active at that moment.","Detectors call `get_lang_hook(lang_name, \"test_coverage\")` without scope; `get_lang_hook` resolves via current implicit scope and may reload module when hook is missing in that scope (`hook_registry.py`), making behavior depend on import order and previous scope state."],"suggestion":"Remove implicit-scope dependence from hook registration/lookup: pass explicit scope keys end-to-end (registration and retrieval), or encapsulate hook state in a runtime context object passed through detector execution. Keep one canonical scope per run and avoid reload-based recovery for normal paths.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"architectural_change","root_cause_cluster":"implicit_process_global_registry_state"},{"dimension":"initialization_coupling","identifier":"coverage_mapping_stale_project_root","summary":"Coverage mapping hardcodes module-level project root and bypasses runtime context","related_files":["desloppify/engine/detectors/coverage/mapping.py","desloppify/core/text_api.py","desloppify/core/_internal/text_utils.py"],"evidence":["`coverage/mapping.py` imports `PROJECT_ROOT` and derives `root_str = str(PROJECT_ROOT) + os.sep` for path trimming.","Runtime root selection is context-aware in `text_utils.get_project_root()` (uses `RuntimeContext.project_root`), but the imported constant path does not consult that runtime context.","This creates initialization-order coupling where path normalization may follow cached/default root rather than active runtime root, especially in tests/multi-root flows."],"suggestion":"Replace `PROJECT_ROOT` constant usage in coverage mapping with per-call `get_project_root()` (or inject project root through function parameters), and avoid deriving runtime paths from module-level constants.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"module","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"implicit_process_global_registry_state"},{"dimension":"initialization_coupling","identifier":"mutable_path_overrides_and_import_snapshot","summary":"Mutable path globals and CLI import-time root snapshot create hidden startup dependencies","related_files":["desloppify/core/paths_api.py","desloppify/cli.py","desloppify/core/runtime_state.py"],"evidence":["`paths_api.py` exposes mutable module globals (`PROJECT_ROOT`, `DEFAULT_PATH`, `SRC_PATH`) that alter path resolution behavior globally.","`cli.py` initializes a module-level `PROJECT_ROOT = get_project_root()` at import time and then branches on sentinel identity in `_resolve_default_path`, coupling path resolution to when the module was imported vs when runtime context is established.","Runtime state already has `ContextVar`-backed scoping (`runtime_state.py`), but path resolution still partly relies on mutable process-level globals/snapshots, increasing startup fragility."],"suggestion":"Deprecate mutable path globals and import-time root snapshots; resolve paths only from runtime context (or explicit command/runtime object) at call time. Consolidate root resolution behind one context-driven API and remove sentinel-based fallback branching.","confidence":"medium","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"architectural_change","root_cause_cluster":"implicit_process_global_registry_state"}],"retrospective":{"root_causes":["Implicit process-global registries and path state are used as control flow, instead of explicit per-run context wiring.","Import-time side effects (decorator registration/hook registration/root snapshots) make correctness depend on load order."],"likely_symptoms":["hook_registry_scope_split_brain","coverage_mapping_stale_project_root","mutable_path_overrides_and_import_snapshot"],"possible_false_positives":["Large/complex synthesis files flagged by structural detectors appear to be maintainability issues, but in this batch they did not present direct initialization-coupling defects."]}}


